        // We need to ensure that (c - k) + (m - k) + x >= k.
        // This simplifies to c + m + x >= 3 * k.
        // Since we chose k = min(c, m, (c + m + x) / 3), the condition c + m + x >= 3 * k is always met.
        // Also, c >= k and m >= k are met by definition of min.
