        //    This happens if m is odd. (n-m) % 2 != (n+m) % 2.
        //    In this case, we cannot use A = n-m axial moves because its parity is wrong.
        //    We need to use at least (n-m)+1 axial moves to satisfy the parity.
        //    So, A = n-m+1.
        //    This means we use one extra axial move.
        //    This extra axial move must be compensated by another axial move in the opposite direction,
